article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 61, Cent. Arkansas 39
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Matt Kingsley scored 12 points and had seven rebounds and Nick Shaw added 11 points to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 61-39 victory over Central Arkansas on Wednesday. The Lumberjacks (20-7, 12-3 Southland) made only 39 percent of their shots in the game, but Central Arkansas only made 22 percent of its shots. The Bears (9-19, 2-13) made only three out of 21 field goals and only one free throw to enter the half down, 33-7. Imad Qahwash led the Bears with 10 points. Kingsley and Shaw were the only two players to reach double figures for the Lumberjacks. Stephen F. Austin led the entire game.
